Dioc

To fix this bug it is necessary to modify destructors in DateChooser and DateChooserButton classes.
The following line should be added in DateChooser's destructor:

qx.locale.Manager.getInstance().removeEventListener("changeLocale", this._updateDatePane, this);

The following line should be added in DateChooserButton's destructor:

qx.locale.Manager.getInstance().removeEventListener("changeLocale", this._changeLocaleHandler, this);

Patches can be applied to mentioned classes to avoid this problem before it is fixed in current trunk/legacy. To do this, the following code should be added somewhere in main function:

qx.Class.patch(qx.ui.component.DateChooser,
    qx.Mixin.define("lle5ui.patch.qx.ui.component.DateChooser",
    {
        destruct : function() {
            qx.locale.Manager.getInstance().removeEventListener("changeLocale", this._updateDatePane, this);
        }
    })
);
qx.Class.patch(qx.ui.component.DateChooserButton,
    qx.Mixin.define("lle5ui.patch.qx.ui.component.DateChooserButton",
    {
        destruct : function() {
            qx.locale.Manager.getInstance().removeEventListener("changeLocale", this._changeLocaleHandler, this);
        }
    })
);


Best wishes,
Denis aka Dioc
